author: Dan H
title: 1998 Flashback
text: Download it off of YouTube, quality should be just as good. Man I hated the Cowboys back in the day . . . now they're just pathetic LOL. "To take from one because it is thought that his own industry and that of his father's has acquired too much, in order to spare to others, who, or whose fathers have not exercised equal industry and skill, is to violate arbitrarily the first principle of association--'the guarantee to every one of a free exercise of his industry and the fruits acquired by it.'" - Thomas Jefferson
